  "prompt": "Is there a website where I can watch Broadway musical videos for free?",
  "response": "While there are limited options for watching full Broadway musical videos for free due to copyright restrictions, you can find various resources that may offer a selection of performances or related content. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many official channels or fans upload clips, performances, and even full shows. Searching for specific musicals might yield good results.\n\n2. **BroadwayHD**: While this is a paid service, it often offers free trials that allow you to watch a variety of Broadway shows during the trial period.\n\n3. **PBS**: PBS often features recorded performances of Broadway musicals and concerts in its programming. Check the PBS website or their streaming service for any available content.\n\n4. **Library Services**: Some public libraries offer access to streaming services like Kanopy, which may have theatrical performances, including some musicals.\n\n5. **Instagram and TikTok**: Short clips, performances, or behind-the-scenes videos are often shared on social media platforms. \n\nAlways ensure you are accessing content legally and respect copyright laws.",
